Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: Frank&#39;s box on TV last night - DEMON! Rosemary
Guiley!!



I was thumbing through Miss Guiley&#39;s &quot;Encyclopedia of Ghosts and 
Spirits,&quot; today, and was happily surprised to see she is aware that 
the Greeks used the word &quot;daimon&quot; in literature (before Christ) - the 
word &quot;daimon&quot; being best defined as &quot;guardian spirits,&quot; and not 
something &quot;evil.&quot; The word &quot;demon&quot; evolved out of this 
word &quot;daimon,&quot; and was turned into something believed to be evil and 
fearful by religion over the last two thousand years. Why can&#39;t this 
truth get out there to the ghost investigating community? I plan on 
writing about this in depth over the next month...I am so tired of 
seeing supposed &quot;experts&quot; on TV using demons to try and frighten 
people with this religious dogma. 

Thanks Rosemary for having this fact in your book under the 
word &quot;demon&quot; - most people are not aware this truth. ;)

LC

