&gt; investigating
&gt; &gt; &gt; an old insane asylum, and they had Chris Moon as a guest 
&gt; &gt; investigator
&gt; &gt; &gt; with the box. You can see the promo clip here:
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; http://www.pennstat eprs.com/ ps_asylum. mov
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; Here&#39;s the site for the show itself:
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; http://www.aetv. com/paranormal- state/index. jsp
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; For those not familiar, its a half hour show that follows along 
&gt; the
&gt; &gt; &gt; &quot;Penn State Paranormal Research Society&quot; and different cases 
they 
&gt; &gt; take
&gt; &gt; &gt; on. Their niche in the &quot;paranormal reality tv show&quot; market is 
that
&gt; &gt; &gt; the group&#39;s leader follows a more Christian orientated skew on
&gt; &gt; &gt; happenings. Lots of &quot;demons&quot; (they have Lorraine Warren guest 
all 
&gt; &gt; the
&gt; &gt; &gt; time), and they usually try to do investigations/ communication 
&gt; only
&gt; &gt; &gt; during what they call &quot;dead time&quot;, 3am-4am, or &quot;the polar 
&gt; opposite 
&gt; &gt; of
&gt; &gt; &gt; 3pm - the time Jesus gave is life for all mankind&quot; as they put 
&gt; it. 
&gt; &gt; Oh,
&gt; &gt; &gt; and they have an &quot;occult specialist&quot; on the team that so far 
has 
&gt; &gt; been
&gt; &gt; &gt; anything but.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; On the positive side, they did actually get (and record for 
later
&gt; &gt; &gt; analysis) live communication on the box in response to 
questions 
&gt; &gt; being
&gt; &gt; &gt; asked. And on the analysis and isolation of the recorded parts, 
&gt; you
&gt; &gt; &gt; could actually hear what was being said (as opposed to the 
usual 
&gt; of
&gt; &gt; &gt; Chris acting as a go-between for very distorted sounds like on 
&gt; those
&gt; &gt; &gt; youtube videos). So it was good to see it a)working in 
the &quot;field&quot;
&gt; &gt; &gt; and b)get some exposure on a tv show.
